# Cisco Packet Tracer: VLAN & Trunking Lab

🌐 Network Topology
[Network Topology](vlan topology.png & trunking topology.png)

## 📝 Project Overview
This lab demonstrates how to configure Virtual Local Area Networks (VLANs) and 802.1Q Trunking to segment network traffic and improve security and efficiency on local area networks.

## 🛠️ Key Configurations Implemented
  VLAN Creation: Segmented network devices into distinct broadcast domains.
  Access Port Assignment: Assigned specific switch ports to their respective VLANs.
  802.1Q Trunking: Configured trunk ports between switches to allow traffic from multiple VLANs to pass through a single physical link.

## 🚀 How to Run the Lab
1. Download the `.pkt` file from this repository.
2. Open it in **Cisco Packet Tracer**.
3. Use the `ping` command or the PDU envelope tool to test connectivity between devices on the same VLAN.
